parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of power, unexpected shifting, or complete loss of gear engagement, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranding.
symptoms: Transmission slips
hesitates
or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to jerk
hesitate
or lose power; unexpected shifting or dropping into lower gear; transmission makes clunking or unusual noises; vehicle feels like it's in neutral; transmission sticks or fails to shift properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear axle failure can cause sudden loss of control, accidents, or stranding, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Rear axle cracks or twists
causing the rear end to drop down to the ground; vehicle becomes difficult to control or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine fires, damage to other components, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the valve cover gasket
oil leaking into the AC compressor
loud clunking noise when shifting transmission
engine stalling
engine fire
oil burning smell
oil leakage
engine sounds like it's trying to cut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine head gasket can cause oil leaks, coolant leaks, and engine damage, leading to engine failure and potentially causing accidents.

coolant leaking from the engine head gasket
engine overheating
engine stalling
engine failure.

transmission fluid leakage
engine stalling
vehicle stalling upon slowing to stop or turn.

engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rocker arm gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to become hard, leading to extended stopping distances, and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard
excessive pressure is needed to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal does not respond normally
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

the ABS system fails to engage properly.
